parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the evaporator core can cause the air conditioning system to malfunction, leading to a loss of cooling, and potentially causing discomfort, distraction, and safety issues while driving, especially in hot weather conditions.
symptoms: The air conditioning system is not operative
the evaporator core is leaking
there is a smell of coolant in the cabin
the AC blows extremely low air
and the AC compressor has been replaced multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Refrigerant leaks can cause the air conditioning system to malfunction, leading to a loss of cooling, and potentially causing discomfort, distraction, and safety issues while driving, especially in hot weather conditions.
symptoms: Refrigerant leaks
AC compressor issues
and high-pressure mode errors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the reverse camera display can cause safety issues, especially at night, as it can block the driver's right front quarter vision.
symptoms: The reverse camera display stays on continuously
even when shifting into forward gear
and cannot be turned off or rebooted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the forward collision alert system can cause safety issues, as it may not provide adequate warning to the driver, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The system does not provide a flashing red display on the windshield when approaching another vehicle at a speed that may cause a collision
even when set to the "far" setting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the backup camera system can cause safety issues, as it may reduce the driver's visibility when reversing, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The backup camera system loses clear vision on the monitor screen during light to heavy rain
and the rear view bumper reflects the sky
reducing rear view vision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the engine start/stop button can cause safety issues, as it may cause the engine to shut off unexpectedly while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The engine shuts off when the hazard button is pressed
and the car must be pulled over
the brake engaged
and the transmission put into park to restart the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the TPMS can lead to a lack of warning for low tire pressure, which can cause tire blowouts, accidents, and loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The TPMS receiver fails to collect information from individual tire pressure sensors
no warning is provided for low tire pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the battery and electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light does not come on when the battery is bad
the vehicle shuts down while driving
the battery fuse block fails
the electrical system shuts down frequently
the engine light comes on
the battery voltage is low.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake problems can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control, especially when the brakes feel spongy or go to the floor.
symptoms: The brakes feel spongy
the brakes go to the floor
a loud metal-to-metal sound is heard when backing up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of sensors and detection systems can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control, especially if the systems are not functioning properly.
symptoms: The side detection device is not working
the sensor is corroded
the system fails to detect obstacles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden shut-down of the vehicle while driving can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down while driving
the engine light comes on
the vehicle restarts with a jerk
the vehicle's electrical system shuts down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission shifting issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, slow down, or stall, leading to potential accidents or loss of control, especially on highways or when merging into traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle rapidly shifts to park and back to the original gear
causing a sudden loss of speed; the transmission skips gears
shudders
or shifts hard; the vehicle loses power or stalls; the transmission slips
bucks
or shifts roughly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, slow down, or stall, leading to potential accidents or loss of control, especially on highways or when merging into traffic.
symptoms: The transmission needs to be replaced
often without any warning signs or dashboard lights; the vehicle shudders or shifts hard when changing gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Stability Control and ABS Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electronic stability control and ABS issues can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to potential accidents or loss of control, especially on highways or when merging into traffic.
symptoms: The STABILITRAK
ABS
and check engine lights come on simultaneously; the vehicle loses power and control
making it difficult to steer or brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The evaporative emission control system leaks can cause the vehicle to pollute the environment and potentially lead to other issues with the vehicle's performance.
symptoms: The EVAP core starts leaking
often without any warning signs or dashboard lights.
